metadata.name: Leviathan #249
metadata.description:
Leviathan is a generative collection of large bodies made form particles, materialised from the viewers own subconscious. Atoms form gargantuan objects - subatomic monoliths and microscopic giants. Playing with the sense of scale it draws on the viewer’s subjective way of associating forms, a pattern that becomes a mirror, a skeleton for them to project. 

Part artist, part viewer. Leviathan asks us to question these relationships of creation, ownership and meaning. It is a chemical reaction that the artist starts and you finish. A colossal dream we are all sharing together - a leviathan.


Controls:
s or double tap: Download image
1 : Download 2400 x 4000
2 : Download 3600 x 6000
3 : Download 4800 x 8000
4 : Download 7200 x 12000

objkt.name: A message through the silk road  #1

metadata.name: A message through the silk road  #1
metadata.description:
This work is part of the "Alphabetic Signs" series.

The "Alphabetic Signs" series finds its roots in different places: in my physical work, in a study on letters and typefaces, but also in graffiti and street art.

In this project I codified 11 new symbols that evoke oriental writing, taking inspiration from Japanese, Chinese and Korean symbols.
I coded a dragged "dirty" brush stroke with drops of color.

I reused the fractal component already used in the previous algorithm by inserting the new symbols and mixing new elements.

it is a work of asemic writing, without any semantic meaning.

This work uses p5.js library and p5.scribble.js library.

metadata.name: Win95 Larvas #113
metadata.description:
Welcome to the Win95 Larvas 🐛

Win95 Larvas is a collaboration with DOS Larvas, a CC0 project on the Tezos Blockchain. 

The Win95 Larvas are a 24x24 px remix of the original DOS Larvas released January 28 2022 on Fx Hash, using the 16 colors available in Windows95.


🐛 Size: 24x24 pixel
🐛 Format: .png
🐛 Colors 16
🐛 Layers: 9
🐛 Traits: 17
🐛 Glitch levels: 5

* Thanks to PureSpider for the great code.

metadata.name: Up Above #56
metadata.description:
This piece is inspired by the feeling of insignificance. This feeling, which we all share and feel at some points in our lives is often referred to as negative. But I feel quite the contrary, this feeling is quite beautiful, as it shows small parts together can form something big.

We are but a speck in the universe, like a grain of sand on a beach, like a single drop of water in an ocean, like a single leaf on a tree. But together we are a forest, a river, a sea. Together we are the universe.

Feel free to explore this piece for as long as you want, and feel free to export it in any way you like, and use it for thing like prints, and, of course, I'd love to know about them :)

---

To export your iteration, click the menu bar at the bottom of the screen and press either the "Export current" or "Export custom" button.

metadata.name: AI Ganora #42
metadata.description:
This artwork is a Digital Collage and Image Compositing

In this Digital Artwork, I have used a combination of CG and artificial intelligence, as well as layers of texture to convey a visual pleasure to the viewer. The random combination of these layers creates an image that an artist may not be able to achieve by himself.

metadata.name: ARAUCO #39
metadata.description:
The Araucaria Araucana, also known as pewén, is a sacred tree for the Mapuche and an emblem of Chile. With an origin dating back 260 million years to the Triassic period, it is part of the oldest forests on the planet. These ancient trees are endangered due to logging, forest fires, and grazing.

ARAUCO is a tribute to araucarias and Mapuche iconography. Incorporating elements such as the Kultrung, the Wünelfe star, and the staggered cross Ngümin, the work displays a typical landscape of southern Chile with the Andes Mountains in the background and the native forest. 

–

Press 's' to export a 4960x7016 PNG file suitable for A2 printing at 300 dpi.

Made with p5js.

Patricio Isaías, September 2022

metadata.name: Petri 1500 v2 QHD  #72
metadata.description:
Petri 1500 is a celebration of reaching 1500 Twitter followers.
As I've grown as an artist what represents that growth but a petri dish, filled with life, finding a way.

There is a bug in the original version that cause display issues on retina & QHD displays. So this version fixes that, is free to all that held a copy at 00:30 14-09-2022 and a few spares for luck.

A sillybration of all things fx(hash) featuring some of my recognisable pallets and primatives
along with something new to me - noise and 'realistic' nature sketches.
All mashed for pure fun.

L to download 1000x1000
S to download 4000x4000
H to download 8000x8000
